# Architectural Documentation

Applies to `3-arch/building-blocks.md`, `3-arch/runtime-views.md`, and feature **Runtime flow**.

**Templates:** [templates.md — 3-arch](../consultation/templates.md#3-arch) · **Gate:** [04-solution-strategy.mdc](04-solution-strategy.mdc)

## Pre-flight — solution strategy gate

Before creating or materially updating building blocks, runtime views, or feature **Blocks** / **Runtime flow**:

1. Run [Ready checklist](04-solution-strategy.mdc#ready-checklist) in [04-solution-strategy.mdc](04-solution-strategy.mdc)
2. On failure — stop; use [Cancel response](04-solution-strategy.mdc#cancel-response); do not proceed to BB/RT steps below

## Building blocks (arc42 §5)

Static decomposition — **prefer relevance over completeness** (important, surprising, risky, complex, volatile blocks only).

| Concept | Meaning |
|---------|---------|
| **Black box** | Outside view — name, responsibility, interfaces |
| **White box** | Internal decomposition shown |
| **Level 1** | Overall system + L1 children |
| **Level 2+** | Zoom selected containers only when justified |

Every block: **Level**, **Parent**, **Type** (`container` / `leaf` / `cross-cutting` / `process`).

**Containment vs dependency:** Contains = white-box child list. Depends on = directed peer need. External systems → **External Systems** section, not internal L1.

**Diagram rules:** Nested subgraphs = containment; one ID per primary level; child IDs extend parent (`BB-02.1`).

### Derive from features

Do not invent blocks unsupported by features, scope, or confirmed interview answers.

**Inputs (order):** `features-list.md` → all `F##_*.md` → `business-scenarios.md` → `solution-strategy.md` → `db-and-dfd.md`.

| Step | Action |
|------|--------|
| 1 Extract | Participants, APIs, stores, cross-cutting capabilities from runtime/UI/data/overview |
| 2 Classify | External → external node; app/service/store → BB |
| 3 Cluster | One block = one purpose; ~5–12 L1 blocks; IDs `BB-01`… |
| 4 Dependencies | calls / pub-sub / read-write from runtime flows |
| 5 Hierarchy | L1 = end-to-end visible; L2+ only when specs decompose further |
| 6 Document | Level, Parent, Type, responsibility, Features, Interfaces, Dependencies |
| 7 Validate | Every F## in a block; every runtime participant mapped |
| 8 Propagate | Feature **Blocks** links; `db-and-dfd.md` |

## Runtime views (arc42 §6)

Every scenario: **trigger**, **block instances** (RT-C09 → `building-blocks.md`), **interactions**, **notable aspects**, **error paths** when significant.

**Include:** multi-block flows; async/consistency; critical integrations; security; ops; significant errors.

**Exclude:** screen layout (UI flow/mockups), business goals (scope), static parts (BB), field-level data (feature + db-and-dfd), tests.

### Two-layer model

| Layer | File |
|-------|------|
| Feature | `F##_*.md` → **Runtime flow** (happy path + feature errors) |
| Architecture | `runtime-views.md` → `RT-##` (cross-feature, external, ops, shared errors) |

Do not duplicate every feature flow in `runtime-views.md`.

### Derive from features

**Inputs (order):** `building-blocks.md` → target `F##_*.md` → `business-scenarios.md` → `features-list.md` → `solution-strategy.md` → existing `runtime-views.md`.

| Step | Action |
|------|--------|
| 1 Identify | UI flow, FR acceptance, data model → scenarios per feature |
| 2 Filter | Keep if: 2+ blocks, async, external, security, ops, significant errors |
| 3 Map | Internal `Name (BB-##)`; external `(external)`; update BB first if missing |
| 4 Notation | Linear → sequenceDiagram; branching → flowchart |
| 5 Place | Feature path → feature file; cross-cutting → `runtime-views.md` |
| 6 Validate | Participants mapped; Must features have runtime or deferral |
| 7 Propagate | `db-and-dfd.md`, `testing-plan.md`, `traceability.md` |
